<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6205> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6205" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "No title preserved. Brutus sent him to Rhodes with thirteen ships. After Philippi he took away the garrison and sailed with Cassius of Parma to join Staius Murcus and Domitius Ahenobarbus (App. BC 5.2). He may be identified with either the C. Clodius who killed C. Antonius (Dio 47.24.2 and 4; see 43, Promagistrates) or the deserter who brought Brutus news of the destruction of Domitius Calvinus' convoy in the Adriatic (Plut. Brut. 47.4)." .
